  "body": "We need to remove this class. : \n\n- the method **isEIP1559** is useless we just need to check if we are in london thanks to the protocol MainnetProtocolSpecs\n- the methods **isForkBlock/getForkBlock** need to be moved to the ProtocolShedule method (like that we will have something generic to retrieve the block number of a fork). To do that we will create a **getMilestoneBlock** method that return the block number of a fork name  : \n\n```java        \npublic interface ProtocolSchedule {\n\n          ProtocolSpec getByBlockNumber(long number);\n\n          public Stream<Long> streamMilestoneBlocks();\n\n          **+++++ public Long getMilestoneBlock(final String forkName);  +++++**\n\n          Optional<BigInteger> getChainId();\n\n          void setTransactionFilter(TransactionFilter transactionFilter);\n\n          void setPublicWorldStateArchiveForPrivacyBlockProcessor(\n            WorldStateArchive publicWorldStateArchive);\n        }\n\n```\n\n- remove **targetGasUsed** method . this method is always used with **computeBaseFee**. So maybe we need to merge this two methods\n\n- **computeBaseFee** method move to BaseFee object for more consistency as a builder. This method will return a BaseFee object directly and not a long\n\n```java\npublic class BaseFee {\n  private final long value;\n  private final long delta;\n  private final long minNextValue;\n  private final long maxNextValue;\n\n  public BaseFee(final FeeMarket feeMarket, final long value) {\n  this.value = value;\n  this.delta = Math.floorDiv(value, feeMarket.getBasefeeMaxChangeDenominator());\n  this.minNextValue = value - delta;\n  this.maxNextValue = value + delta;\n  }\n\n  ....\n\n  ++++ public static BaseFee computeBaseFee(\n      ++++ final FeeMarket feeMarket\n      final long blockNumber,\n      final long parentBaseFee,\n      final long parentBlockGasUsed,\n      final long targetGasUsed) {\n       ...\n      return new new BaseFee(feeMarket, baseFee);\n  }\n}\n```",
